post_text: Important SCAM ALERT from the Manchester Police...
shared_text:
Manchester Police
August 24 at 2:57 PM ·

🚨SCAM ALERT🚨

We received early reports of a Manchester Township School District job posting listed on Indeed.com. We can confirm that this job posting is NOT legitimate and ask that you DO NOT APPLY. After applying to the Administrative Assistant position, the potential applicant is sent an e-mail (from a Google Mail account) which requests personal information from the applicant and given tasks involving money and purchasing items. Please stay vigilant when searching for jobs online.

⚠️ Here are some warning signs to look out for when searching for a job online:

1. The e-mail address does not match the company’s name and does not use the company’s domain name.

2. The job posting is vague and the wording is not well written.

3. “No experience necessary”

4. The “recruiter” asks for your personal information through e-mail or a non-secure server.

5. The “recruiter” tasks you with an assignment involving money, checks, or purchasing items for the company.

6. The “recruiter” asks for money from the applicant.

7. If the job posting seems too good to be true, it most likely is.

post_text: A message from our mayor about power outages...
shared_text:
Ken Palmer, Mayor of Manchester
August 6 at 3:21 PM ·

Currently, we have 4,200 residences still without power. JCpL does have crews through out Manchester. I understand CW 5 has recently been restored. I know people have received a 8/11 timeframe from JCPL for all to be restored. Please know, that’s when they estimate all service calls to be completed. I just finished a conference call with JCPL and other Mayors where they indicated 85 percent of all residents will be restored by Friday at midnight.

For those residents without power and need to go somewhere cool and air conditioned, you can go to the Whiting Firehouse and/or the Civic Center at Manchester Town Hall... both locations are open 4:00 pm to 8:00 pm today. Each day thereafter the cooling stations will be open from 8:00 am to 8:00 pm.

I will provide more information when I receive it.

post_text: The Ocean County Library is now open with limited hours. See below for details.
shared_text:
Ocean County Library is sharing a COVID-19 Update.
July 5 at 2:00 PM ·

As we welcome you back to our branches on Monday, July 6th, here are some things to expect:

When patrons enter the buildings they will notice a few changes in the buildings. Our service desks include desk shields, masks are required in all library buildings, and our staff will also be wearing PPE. All materials returned will be quarantined for the recommended length of time set by public health officials, after which they will be checked in and added back to our collection. Overdue fines will not accrue on materials during this time.

Branches will have limited hours and services. We will provide access to public PCs by appointment. Due to the limited number of PCs available to provide social distancing, computer use will be reduced to one half hour per day. Seating is limited to allow for social distancing. Additionally, short-term browsing will be allowed; we ask that customers are mindful of those wishing to use the library and limit their time spent in our libraries due to the reduced 25% capacity.

For more information, visit our website: www.theoceancountylibrary.org

post_text: Please see below from the Booster Club. Thank you for doing this for our athletes!
shared_text:
Manchester Township High School Booster Club
June 8 at 12:12 PM ·

Good morning! We hope everyone is doing great! Just a friendly reminder that this Thursday June 11 at 6:30 pm will be our celebration for our senior Band/Drama/Color Guard members and Athletes.
The link for this can be accessed Thursday at 6:30 on the HS Athletic page (https://www.manchestertwp.org/MTHS/Athletics)as well as here,the Manchester Township High School Booster Club’s Twitter and Instagram pages.
The event will feature the reading of profiles for those who rsvp’d as well as drawing for prizes and a video montage created especially for them.
They will receive a custom made booklet with their profile, a Hawk flash drive containing the montage, a personalized plaque and the prize that was drawn for them. Items will be available for pick up within the next couple weeks. (Due to Covid some items have been delayed). Will keep you posted.
For Senior Athletes, members of Band,Drama or Color guard who didn’t RSVP , they also will receive a small prize as well as the others item. GO HAWKS!

post_text: Thank you Booster Club for hosting a virtual senior athlete celebration! Details in their post below. Please direct questions to the Booster Club.
shared_text:
Manchester Township High School Booster Club
April 30 at 8:41 PM ·

🎼🎹🎺🎷🥁⚽️🏀⚾️⚾️🥎🎾🏐🏑🥍⛳️🤸🏽‍♀️🏊🏼‍♀️🥇We at the Booster Club hope all is well with you and you’re families during these unprecedented times. In keeping with tradition the best we can while Covid 19 restrictions are still in place and the uncertainty of comfortable social gatherings, we will be hosting a virtual celebration of our Senior Hawk Athletes on Thursday June 11th at 6:30. (Platform to be announced at a later date) The senior athletes should have received an email(in their school email) with both an invitation and a profile sheet that needs to be filled out and returned NO LATER than May 15th as we are having memory books made. I believe the district also emailed the parents with the same info. Please disregard the event date in the original email as there was a typo(sorry☺️). We look forward to a night celebrating these fine athletes!

shared_text:
Manchester Twp. PTA
April 26 at 6:33 PM ·

Here is the slate of officers from the Nominating Committee, for the Manchester PTA for the 2020-2021 School Year! You will notice there are a few vacancies. We don’t want that! Maybe you would consider volunteering to run from the floor?

Anyone wishing to run ‘from the Floor’ for office must submit their "Intent to run" in writing. The written notice must be sent to the PTA President, the Recording Secretary and the Nominations Chairperson: 20 days before the Membership/Voting Virtual meeting, which is May 28th @ 7pm. Send contact information, position & info. about what makes you best for the position you are applying for to Nominations@Manchesterpta.org. It will be forwarded to the President, Secretary and Nominations.

Please note that submitting an "Intent to run" is NOT a Nomination. You and/or someone to represent you must be at the Voting Meeting and verbally nominate you at this meeting in order for you to be added to the ballot.

Check our Website www.Manchesterpta.org for Meeting dates and Officer & Chairperson descriptions.
text:
Manchester Twp. PTA
April 26 at 6:33 PM ·

Here is the slate of officers from the Nominating Committee, for the Manchester PTA for the 2020-2021 School Year! You will notice there are a few vacancies. We don’t want that! Maybe you would consider volunteering to run from the floor?

Anyone wishing to run ‘from the Floor’ for office must submit their "Intent to run" in writing. The written notice must be sent to the PTA President, the Recording Secretary and the Nominations Chairperson: 20 days before the Membership/Voting Virtual meeting, which is May 28th @ 7pm. Send contact information, position & info. about what makes you best for the position you are applying for to Nominations@Manchesterpta.org. It will be forwarded to the President, Secretary and Nominations.

Please note that submitting an "Intent to run" is NOT a Nomination. You and/or someone to represent you must be at the Voting Meeting and verbally nominate you at this meeting in order for you to be added to the ballot.

Check our Website www.Manchesterpta.org for Meeting dates and Officer & Chairperson descriptions.

Manchester Recreation
April 21 at 8:36 AM ·

Today's project: Magic Milk
Materials:
Milk
Food Coloring
Flat Bowl
Q-tip
Dawn Dish Soap

1. In a flat bowl pour about an inch of milk and then drop food coloring randomly in the milk
2. Dip a Q-tip in Dawn Dish Soap and then dip the Q-tip in the milk and watch the magic happen!

Post pictures and videos of your Magic Milk Project. We would love to see your project!!!

"The Tree Frog"

post_text: 🎼🎤"Gonna learn from home through technology.We’re gonna help each other virtually." Whiting School Principal Mrs. Swift and her daughter Brianna bringing us some musical inspiration!
shared_text:
Briana Swift is with Evelyn Swift.
March 30 at 6:08 PM ·

My mom is the best educator I know so when she asked for help making a song I tried to deliver. Hope you all enjoy. Especially the students of Manchester Township who we miss dearly!

Song-Old Town Road

*we do not own the copyright to this music* just the lyrics!

Oh your gonna learn from home
Through technology
We’re gonna help each other virtually

Even though things aren’t the same
We just want you all to know
That we’re still here to support you
Even all the way from home

We are so proud of your efforts
You’ve been doing very well
With the help of your parents
Things are going very swell

Even though we really miss you
It is best that we be safe
We just want you all healthy
At the end of the day.

So just remember one thing
All you can do is your best
When we return to school
We will handle all the rest.

❤️

post_text: And for the older readers, To Kill a Mockingbird or The Outsiders?
shared_text:
Ocean County Library created a poll.
March 24 at 12:00 PM ·

"To Kill a Mockingbird" vs "The Outsiders"
A battle of firsts, these two works were the publishing debuts of both authors. Lee wrote "To Kill a Mockingbird" at age 34 while S.E. Hinton wrote "The Outsiders" at only 16 years of age. Both books would go on to be made into popular films, with "To Kill a Mockingbird" receiving three Academy Awards.
Which novel will move on? Choose your favorite before voting is locked at noon EST tomorrow, March 25.

Check out these titles in our OverDrive collection!
"The Outsiders": https://ocl.overdrive.com/search?query=outsiders+hinton
"To Kill a Mockingbird" and more from Harper Lee:
https://ocl.overdrive.com/search?query=harper%20lee&subject=26

post_text: The library wants to know! Cat in the Hat or Green Eggs and Ham? Take their poll.
shared_text:
Ocean County Library created a poll.
March 24 at 12:00 PM ·

Our first match-up from the "Children's Titles" division:
A battle of classics by the only author to be featured twice in this year's Book Bracket. Theodor Geisel, aka Dr. Seuss, wrote "The Cat in the Hat" as a result of a challenge to write a book using a list of 225 words. Succeeding at that, he then wrote "Green Eggs and Ham" using only 50.
Choose your favorite before voting is locked at noon EST tomorrow, March 25.

Looking for more Dr. Seuss? Check out our OverDrive collection available from home or on the go at https://ocl.overdrive.com/search?query=seuss

Ocean County Parks & Recreation
March 18 at 7:00 PM ·

ATTENTION: Parents, Teachers, Students
Join us for our first Facebook Live session this Friday, March 20th at 11am. We will be broadcasting LIVE from Cattus Island County Park with "Box Turtle Talk."
We will show off one of our Eastern Box Turtles and discuss the many things that make this fairly common turtle so interesting. This is perfect for kids out of school and at home due to the current health concerns.. These ongoing mini "Science Lessons" will continue weekly with different topics and locations.
STAY TUNED.

March 18 at 7:00 PM ·

ATTENTION: Parents, Teachers, Students
Join us for our first Facebook Live session this Friday, March 20th at 11am. We will be broadcasting LIVE from Cattus Island County Park with "Box Turtle Talk."
We will show off one of our Eastern Box Turtles and discuss the many things that make this fairly common turtle so interesting. This is perfect for kids out of school and at home due to the current health concerns.. These ongoing mini "Science Lessons" will continue weekly with different topics and locations.
STAY TUNED.
